USB BLOCK:

1.Click Group policy management
2.Expand Forest name
3.Right click Domain name
4.Creat New GPO
5.Name(USB BLOCKED)
6.Right click new gpo name
7.Click edit
8. User config:     policy>Administrative template>system-Removeable storege access
  Computer config:  policy>Administrative template>system-Removeable storege access
8.Click Removeable storege access:Deny all access
9.Click enable
10.In the Group Policy Management console, select your Disable USB Acce ss policy.
11.In the Security Filtering section, add t he Domain Admins group.
12.Go to the Delegation tab and click the Advanced in the security settings editor, specify that the domain
Admins group is not allowed to apply this GPO ( Apply group policy Deny)
13.Work Finished
